title: Loose moose leaps over car on residential street
text:
Blake Griffin has nothing on this moose.
Watch as a loose moose wanders through the streets of Manchester, N.H., and leaps over a Honda Civic.
OK, so maybe the moose didn’t dunk a basketball after performing the leap, but still.
Let’s just hope the moose didn’t encounter any rivals along the way.
As it turns out, all ended well for the moose. From WMUR in Manchester:
Manchester police responded to the area and worked to guide the animal back into the wild.
Police Chief Nick Willard tweeted that the moose was last seen along the power lines heading safely into the woods of Goffstown.
